summary: Completed backend testing of Multi-Manufacturer GPS CSV Import feature. All 44 tests pass (26 unit tests + 18 API integration tests). Successfully tested Catapult, STATSports, PlayerTek, and GPEXE CSV import with auto-detection, delimiter handling, European decimals, and data normalization.
context_for_next_testing_agent: GPS CSV Import feature fully implemented and tested. Backend module at /app/backend/gps_import/ handles multi-manufacturer CSV parsing with auto-detection of Catapult, STATSports, PlayerTek, GPEXE formats. Supports semicolon delimiters and European decimal separators. API tests in /app/backend/tests/test_csv_import_api.py cover all endpoints.

GET_supported_providers.details: Returns 4 manufacturers (catapult, statsports, playertek, gpexe) and canonical metrics categories

POST_preview_catapult.details: Correctly detects 'catapult' manufacturer and maps columns (Player Load, Total Distance, etc.)

POST_preview_statsports.details: Correctly detects 'statsports' from Dynamic Stress Load and HSR columns

POST_preview_playertek.details: Correctly detects 'playertek' from PlayerTek column signature

POST_preview_gpexe.details: Correctly handles semicolon delimiter and comma decimal separators (8200,5 -> 8200.5)

POST_import_catapult.details: Successfully imports 3 records from Catapult CSV, stores in gps_data collection

POST_import_statsports.details: Successfully imports 2 records from STATSports CSV

POST_import_gpexe.details: Successfully handles semicolon delimiter and European decimal format

max_speed_conversion.details: max_speed is stored in m/s (32.5 km/h correctly converted to ~9.03 m/s)

imported_record_fields.details: Imported records have correct fields: athlete_id, coach_id, session_id, total_distance, source, device

auth_required.details: Both preview and import endpoints return 403 without authentication

api_integration_tests.coverage: All 3 endpoints with all 4 manufacturer formats
